Headless-env fix for M28AI (vendored, gitignored under /M28AI).

M28Events.lua:ProjectileFiredAtGunship sums incoming projectile damage but
falls back to the STRING 'nil' when a projectile's DamageData.DamageAmount is
unset, so `number + 'nil'` throws "perform arithmetic on ... got string". In
late-game air battles this fires per-projectile-per-gunship and explodes to
~30k errors/game, flooding the sim log (contaminating perf profiles) and
disabling M28's gunship-refuel micro. Fallback should be 0, not 'nil'.

Apply from repo root:  git apply patches/m28ai-gunship-damageamount.patch
(or edit M28AI/lua/AI/M28Events.lua line ~1753 by hand)

--- a/M28AI/lua/AI/M28Events.lua
+++ b/M28AI/lua/AI/M28Events.lua
@@ -1750,7 +1750,7 @@
         if oCurProjectile:BeenDestroyed() then
             table.remove(oTarget[M28UnitInfo.reftoEnemyProjectiles], iCurProjectile)
         else
-            iTotalDamage = iTotalDamage + (oCurProjectile.DamageData.DamageAmount or 'nil')
+            iTotalDamage = iTotalDamage + (oCurProjectile.DamageData.DamageAmount or 0)
         end
     end
 
